                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50A/153: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 21, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. Your 530 [<hi rend="italic">531</hi>], September 19, 9 a.m., fourth
                    sentence. You understand of course that, as stated in Hamilton’s letter of July
                        27,<note n="99" xml:id="d679fn99">Not printed.</note> the Americans in
                    question have no official status vis-à-vis this Government.</p>
                <p>Sent to Chungking only.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
